    {
      "name": "📦 Bulk Upload",
      "description": "Upload CSV to create multiple products + variants at once.\n\nOrder:\n1. Upload Clean CSV (gets id → saved as bulk_upload_id)\n2. Poll Status until completed\n3. Upload Error Test CSV → verify error report\n4. Download Error Report\n5. List Past Uploads\n\n⚠️ Celery worker must be running:\n  celery -A config worker --loglevel=info",
      "item": [

        {
          "name": "Upload Clean CSV (24 variants, 4 products)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 202 Accepted', () => pm.response.to.have.status(202));",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Has upload id', () => pm.expect(json).to.have.property('id'));",
                  "pm.test('Has poll_url', () => pm.expect(json).to.have.property('poll_url'));",
                  "pm.environment.set('bulk_upload_id', json.id);",
                  "console.log('Bulk upload started. ID:', json.id);",
                  "console.log('Poll URL:', json.poll_url);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                {
                  "key": "file",
                  "type": "file",
                  "src": [],
                  "description": "⚠️ SELECT trendio_bulk_test.csv\n\nSteps:\n1. Click the file icon next to this row\n2. Navigate to and select: trendio_bulk_test.csv\n3. Do NOT set Content-Type header manually"
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/products/bulk-upload/",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["products", "bulk-upload", ""]
            },
            "description": "⚠️ CRITICAL — Postman setup:\n\n1. Body tab → select 'form-data'\n2. Key: file\n3. Click the 'Text' dropdown on the right → change to 'File'\n4. Click 'Select Files' → choose trendio_bulk_test.csv\n5. Headers tab → make sure NO Content-Type is set manually\n\nExpected response (HTTP 202):\n{\n  \"id\": \"uuid\",\n  \"status\": \"uploaded\",\n  \"message\": \"Upload received. Processing started in the background.\",\n  \"poll_url\": \"/api/v1/products/bulk-upload/uuid/\"\n}\n\nThe id is auto-saved to bulk_upload_id environment variable."
          }
        },

        {
          "name": "Poll Status — Check Progress",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Has status field', () => pm.expect(json).to.have.property('status'));",
                  "console.log('--- Bulk Upload Status ---');",
                  "console.log('Status:    ', json.status);",
                  "console.log('Total:     ', json.total_records);",
                  "console.log('Processed: ', json.processed);",
                  "console.log('Success:   ', json.success_count);",
                  "console.log('Failed:    ', json.failure_count);",
                  "if (json.status === 'completed') {",
                  "  console.log('✅ Upload completed!');",
                  "  if (json.error_file_url) {",
                  "    pm.environment.set('error_file_url', json.error_file_url);",
                  "    console.log('⚠️ Error report:', json.error_file_url);",
                  "  }",
                  "} else if (json.status === 'failed') {",
                  "  console.log('❌ Upload failed');",
                  "} else {",
                  "  console.log('⏳ Still processing — run this request again in 2-3 seconds');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/products/bulk-upload/{{bulk_upload_id}}/",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["products", "bulk-upload", "{{bulk_upload_id}}", ""]
            },
            "description": "Poll this every 2-3 seconds until status = 'completed' or 'failed'.\n\nExpected final response for clean CSV:\n{\n  \"status\": \"completed\",\n  \"total_records\": 24,\n  \"processed\": 4,\n  \"success_count\": 24,\n  \"failure_count\": 0,\n  \"error_file_url\": null\n}\n\nCheck Celery terminal to watch live processing logs."
          }
        },

        {
          "name": "Upload Error Test CSV (expect 3 ok, 4 failed)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 202 Accepted', () => pm.response.to.have.status(202));",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.environment.set('bulk_upload_id', json.id);",
                  "console.log('Error test upload started. ID:', json.id);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                {
                  "key": "file",
                  "type": "file",
                  "src": [],
                  "description": "SELECT trendio_error_test.csv\nThis file has 4 intentional bad rows to test error reporting."
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/products/bulk-upload/",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["products", "bulk-upload", ""]
            },
            "description": "Select trendio_error_test.csv.\n\nThis CSV has intentional errors:\n- Row 3: missing title\n- Row 4: sale_price > base_price\n- Row 5: missing SKU\n- Row 7: duplicate SKU\n\nExpected after polling:\n{\n  \"status\": \"completed\",\n  \"success_count\": 3,\n  \"failure_count\": 4,\n  \"error_file_url\": \"http://localhost:8000/media/csvs/errors/..._errors.csv\"\n}"
          }
        },

        {
          "name": "Poll Status — Error Test (wait for completed)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
